*All towns and cities in Kings County were annexed to the [[City of Brooklyn]] starting in 1854 with Bushwick and Williamsburgh and ending with the last remaining town- Flatlands in 1896. At that point the city of Brooklyn and Kings County were coterminous.<ref name=Times/> In 1898 the city and county would be annexed to the city of [[City of Greater New York|New York]] as the [[Borough (New York City)|borough]] of Brooklyn and remain Kings County.<ref name=Consolidation/>

